HEADWORD: Shooter
<hw>Shoot"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who shoots, as an archer or a gunner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which shoots.</def> Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A firearm; <as>as, a five-<ex>shooter</ex></as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq. U.S.]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A shooting star.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shooting</ent>⟦br⟧
